        "senderName": "NWS Missoula MT",
        "headline": "Frost Advisory issued June 7 at 11:35AM MDT until June 8 at 9:00AM MDT by NWS Missoula MT",
        "description": "* WHAT...Temperatures between 30 to 36 degrees will result in frost\nformation. Localized cold spots could reach into the upper 20s.\n\n* WHERE...In Idaho, Orofino/Grangeville Region, Southern Clearwater\nMountains, Eastern Lemhi County, and Northern Clearwater Mountains.\nIn Montana, Flathead/Mission Valleys, Kootenai/Cabinet Region,\nLower Clark Fork Region, and Missoula/Bitterroot Valleys.\n\n* WHEN...From midnight MDT /11 PM PDT/ tonight to 9 AM MDT /8 AM PDT/\nMonday.\n\n* IMPACTS...Frost could harm sensitive outdoor vegetation. Sensitive\noutdoor plants may be killed if left uncovered.",
        "instruction": "Take steps now to protect tender plants from the cold.",
